What you need to know:

Just like the seventh leg at Nyali Golf and Country Club, the focus this week will be on in-form Zimbabwean pro Robson Chinhoi who has become a big threat to local prosBeing at home, Snow, who won at Muthaiga with an impressive score of 13 under par last season, is likely to play well and offer Chinhoi a strong challengeMeanwhile joining the tour for the first time, is Zambia’s Dayne Moore, a regular Sunshine Tour player, while other new faces are Ghana’s Issah Adams, Malawi’s Visitor Mapwanya and Victor Kachepatsonga